subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
Male cerci short, parallel to epiproct (
Fig. 8D
), tapering towards the acute apex (
Fig. 8C
); apical valves of aedeagus with distal half slender, curved inwards, touching each other at apex (
Fig. 10E
). Sheath of aedeagus with well-developed mid-dorsal lobes (
Fig. 10E
), covering most of the apical valves (
Fig. 10D
); dorsal hump slightly prominent (
Fig. 10D
). Lophi of epiphallus widely expanded towards the posterior process of the lateral plates (dorsal view) (
Fig. 10F
). Lateral carinae of pronotum slightly indicated. Hind tibiae greenish or orange (
Fig. 6G
).
